sec.p:
An essential part of each calibration is to perform cross-validation, that is, to repeat the experiments several times, removing a different portion of the samples at each repetition. The MSE (equation (2)) was used to assess the capacity of the model to be calibrated, as well as its capacity to make accurate prediction. It is the root mean square difference between the estimated values (
Y^i
) and the actual values (
Yi
).

Sensitivity analyses were performed on the number of trucks included in each training and test split. Therefore, the estimated values (
Y^i
) are the simulated generation rate per truck and the actual values (
Yi
) are the truck collected weight data.
